main event: Two UFO sightings were reported by the Colombian Navy in Cartagena, Colombia on 19th October 1959, with the objects appearing slightly darker and larger than stars, resembling artificial satellites.
interesting points: The Colombian Navy reported two sightings, with the first sighting at 270 azimuth on 19/1158Z.
The objects were described as slightly darker and larger than stars, resembling artificial satellites.
No additional data was given for the second sighting, leading to insufficient data for evaluation.
The report indicates perfect visibility and a clear description of the appearance of the UFOs.
There is a transmission message indicating the relay of the UFO sightings to the U.S. Air Force and other relevant authorities.
sighted object: two UFOs appearing as artificial satellites
photographs: no photograph included in the report
